        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the best free SEO tool in 2026?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Google Search Console is the best free SEO tool overall. It provides first-party click and impression data directly from Google — real rankings, real traffic, real CTR — with no sampling or estimation. Every site owner should use it, regardless of what other tools they have.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can free SEO tools replace paid ones?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">For basic tasks, yes. Google's free tools cover search performance, keyword research, traffic analysis, and speed testing. Competitive research, bulk analysis, and automated reporting require paid plans. Start with free tools and upgrade when the time savings justify the cost.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Which free tool is best for keyword research?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Google Keyword Planner offers the most reliable free data — sourced directly from Google with unlimited queries. AnswerThePublic excels at question-based content ideas. Semrush's free tier provides 10 searches daily with difficulty scores and intent data for competitive validation.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How many free SEO tools do I need?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Start with three: Google Search Console for performance data, Google Analytics 4 for traffic analysis, and Google Keyword Planner for keyword research. Add Screaming Frog for technical audits on larger sites and Yoast for WordPress on-page optimization as needed.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
